title: District 11 girls tennis doubles finals to have Bethlehem feel
text:
Madelyn Conrad, along with Samantha Peterson, will look to bring home doubles gold for Liberty on Monday. (lehighvalleylive.com file photo) By Josh Folck | For lehighvalleylive.com on October 18, 2015 3:08 PM View/Post Comments 
The Bethlehem schools will be well represented in Monday's District 11 girls tennis doubles championships at Lehigh University. 
The Liberty and Freedom rivalry will be showcased at 12:30 p.m. as top-seeded Samantha Peterson and Madelyn Conrad of the Hurricanes square off against the second-seeded Patriots team of Natalie Sinai and Kaitlyn Swint in the Class AAA final.
